The new owner of microblogging app Twitter and CEO of Tesla Motors, Elon Musk has tweeted a disturbing post, suggesting that his life might be cut short. Though he did not give full details of what his fears are, the billionaire hinted his life may be threatened. In what seems to be a gesture of lack of regret, Musk declares that it has been nice getting to know “you”.   How to become a good cross dresser, by Bobrisky     I’m not bi-s3xual, says ex-BBNaija’s Emmanuel     Why parents should pay well for children’s schools…   Although it is still unclear who “you’ in this situation refers to, speculations are that he is referring to netizens who have shown him a lot of support. He tweeted: “If I die under mysterious circumstances, it’s been nice knowing ya” “When confronted by a fan that his response was unpalatable Musk says he will do his best to stay alive.” The fan said: “That’s not funny,” To which he replied “Sorry! I will do my best to stay alive.” Attachments area